The paper focuses on dynamic spectrum sharing, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also leverages social intelligence and information sharing among secondary users, which suggests a potential fit for cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The imitation-based mechanism proposed in the paper involves estimating expected throughput and channel selection, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also mentions convergence to an equilibrium, which could relate to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
